   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_936_1826_01_04_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <note place="bottom">January 4<lb/>
                  1826<lb/>
               </note>
               <salute>
                  <persName>My dear Miss Edgeworth.</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
               I send you
               <title ref="./Workography.xml#Janus1">
                  <hi rend="underline">Janus</hi> an annual volume</title> in which<lb/>
               you will find the delightful essay you<lb/>
               entrusted to my care when I had the<lb/>
               pleasure of being under the roof of<lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths town</placeName>. The preliminary memoir<lb/>
               was not inserted, the Editor thinking the<lb/>
               paper rather long for such a work at any<lb/>
               rate. It is safe among my papers<lb/>
               but these have not yet followed me<lb/>
               hither from <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#STK">Scotland</placeName>.<lb/>
               I fear the volume is rather <unclear>of too</unclear>
               <lb/>
               serious a complexion. <hi rend="underline">Many</hi> things in it<lb/>
               are, however, good - and that is more I<lb/>
               think that can be said of any of the<lb/>
               other works of the same class we have<lb/>
               as yet seen here. I have marked with<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_936_1826_01_04_page02.jpg"/>
               a cross in the Index one or two<lb/>
               articles contributed by myself - And<lb/>
               shall be happy in receiving your<lb/>
               permission to say that you will give<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BoydX1">Mr Boyd</persName> something for the next<lb/>
               volume he publishes.<lb/>
               I enclose also a Bank Post Bill<lb/>
               for £25 which <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BoydX1">Mr Boyd</persName> has sent<lb/>
               to me as his acknowledgement of the<lb/>
               <title ref="./Workography.xml#Thoug1">Chapter on Bores</title>.<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockS1">My wife</persName> has stood her journey<lb/>
               to London well &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ2">Johnny</persName> also<lb/>
               is thriving tolerably. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockS1">Sophia</persName> sends<lb/>
               you &amp; her friends with you her<lb/>
               Loves &amp; compliments of <hi rend="underline">1826</hi>.<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ScotW1">Sir Walter Scott</persName> has had a<lb/>
               slight illness lately but is now<lb/>
               quite reestablished at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Abbotsford-House_STK">Abbotsford</placeName>.<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_936_1826_01_04_page03.jpg"/>
               I beg to be remembered to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                  <lb/>
               Edgeworth</persName>, <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">Mr Edgeworth</persName>, and<lb/>
               the rest of the household with<lb/>
               whom I spent days not to be<lb/>
               forgotten, &amp; remain always<lb/>
               most sincerely yours<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">JG Lockhart</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Pall-Mall-25_ENK">25 Pall Mall</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName> -<lb/>
                  Jan<hi rend="superscript">y</hi> 4. 1826<lb/>
                  <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_936_1826_01_04_page04.jpg"/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">Lockhart</persName>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
